    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "narration_text": "A patient's leukemia has relapsed three times. Each treatment inflicted DNA damage. Each time, a new population survived.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B01.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.71,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B01.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B01.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "act": "COLD OPEN",
      "narration_text": "By the third relapse, these leukemic B cells have one defining feature: they refuse to die.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "STILL",
        "source": "ai",
        "motion": "kenburns",
        "focus": [
          0.5,
          0.4
        ],
        "remotion": {
          "pattern": "SlateCard",
          "provenance": "proven-core/SlateCard",
          "version": "1",
          "props": {
            "headline": "By the third relapse, these leukemic B cells have one defining\u2026",
            "eyebrow": "COLD OPEN",
            "topic": "CANCER BIOLOGY"
          },
          "rendered": {
            "out": "media/B02.mp4",
            "at": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.0,
      "viz": {
        "prompt_seed": "bone marrow biopsy microscopy slide showing dense clusters of abnormal lymphocytes, clinical pathology, editorial treatment"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 5.98,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B02.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B02.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "THE QUESTION",
      "narration_text": "Chemotherapy inflicts enough DNA damage to trigger apoptosis in normal cells. Here the same damage does not kill the leukemic cells. Why does the death signal arrive but not execute?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.65,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "narration_text": "Apoptosis \u2014 programmed cell death \u2014 runs through the mitochondria. DNA damage triggers a signal. That signal should open a pore in the mitochondrial membrane. Cytochrome c escapes. Caspases execute death.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 14.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "circuit",
        "note": "Intrinsic pathway spine: damage -> signal -> BCL-2 balance -> MOMP -> caspases -> death. All teal, flowing left to right. This is the intact, working circuit."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 15.28,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "narration_text": "In a healthy cell, that circuit runs cleanly. The leukemic cell has the same circuit. The signal arrives. But something is intercepting it.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "circuit_blocked",
        "note": "Same circuit, now with a crimson STOP block appearing at the BCL-2 balance node. Signal arrives left; nothing exits right."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.12,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B05.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B05.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM \u2014 section card",
      "narration_text": "Five sabotage points. Each one a separate defense. Each one selected by a chemotherapy exposure.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 6.16,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B06.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B06.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Sabotage one: BCL-2 overexpression. BCL-2 is a guardian protein. It grabs BAX \u2014 the mitochondrial pore-opener \u2014 and holds it. No BAX free, no pore, no death.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "sabotage_accumulate",
        "note": "Intrinsic circuit. A crimson BLOCKER labeled 'BCL-2 HIGH' appears at the MOMP node, snapping into place. BAX held, no pore."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.43,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Sabotage two: BAX is lost. Some cells don't just hold BAX \u2014 they delete it. No effector protein at all. Even if BCL-2 is beaten, nothing is there to punch through the membrane.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "sabotage_accumulate",
        "note": "Second crimson BLOCKER labeled 'BAX LOST' appears at effector position. Circuit now has two blocks."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.52,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Sabotage three: IAPs \u2014 inhibitor of apoptosis proteins. Even if MOMP occurs, caspases must activate to execute death. IAPs \u2014 specifically XIAP \u2014 block them directly at the execution stage.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "sabotage_accumulate",
        "note": "Third crimson BLOCKER labeled 'XIAP' appears at caspase node. Three blocks on circuit now."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 16.74,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Sabotage four: PI3K-AKT survival signaling. AKT phosphorylates BAD \u2014 a pro-apoptotic protein \u2014 inactivating it. Less pressure on BCL-2. The guardian's job gets easier.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "sabotage_accumulate",
        "note": "Fourth crimson BLOCKER labeled 'AKT-BAD' appears at BH3-only sensor node. Four blocks."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 13.64,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "narration_text": "Sabotage five: p53 mutation. p53 is the hub that links DNA damage to the apoptotic signal. Remove p53, and the damage sensor fires \u2014 but the message never reaches the mitochondria.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "sabotage_accumulate",
        "note": "Fifth crimson BLOCKER labeled 'p53 MUT' appears at p53/sensor node. All five blocks now on circuit. The complete sabotage map."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 14.47,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B11.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B11.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "narration_text": "Five defenses. Not one, five. A drug that hits one of them leaves four others intact. The death signal still cannot push through.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "five_blocks_static",
        "note": "Full five-block circuit held. Pause. GOLD signal arrow attempts to cross from left; stops at first block. Emphasizes redundancy."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.12,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B12.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B12.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "narration_text": "Here is how selection built it. A leukemic clone. Exposure one: most cells die. BCL-2-high cells survive \u2014 selected.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 11.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "clonal_selection",
        "note": "Many teal dots (cells); crimson selection pressure; most disappear; one BCL-2-high dot remains enlarged. Label: 'BCL-2 HIGH \u2014 SELECTED.' Illustrative."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B13.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.69,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B13.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B13.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B14",
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "narration_text": "Exposure two: the surviving BCL-2-high clone is hit again. Now cells that have also lost BAX survive. Exposure three: IAP levels rise in the survivors.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "viz": {
        "pattern": "clonal_selection_step2",
        "note": "Staircase continues. Step 2 adds 'BAX LOST'; Step 3 adds 'XIAP UP'. Each step narrows the surviving clone but hardens it. Illustrative."
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B14.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.65,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/clips/B14.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-apoptosis-resistance/mp3/beat-B14.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B15",
      "act": "RECAP",
      "narration_text": "The death signal arrives. It always did. The cancer cell has spent three rounds of chemotherapy building a five-layer wall against it. CANCER BIOLOGY.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
